I put some things in their lunchbox some times that they aren't always super excited about. I'm ok with that. They have learned that you get what you get some times and from that, they've learned that their tastes also change. If they truly hate it, they tell me and we'll still eat it up and then take a break. My kids are just like any other kids that would rather have Willy Wonka pack their lunch, but I'm also the mom. And variety and nutrition come first. Today's lunch is a veggie burger on flat bread, peanut butter puffs (this is the one they aren't fans of), pears and chocolate hummus.
